// useDiagram
// Provides access to the diagram list and CRUD operations from the session store.

A thin facade over the session store; no local state. All mutations are delegated to the store.

FUNCTION useDiagram() -> UseDiagramReturn                                       EXPORT
  CALLS: useSessionStore (sessionStore)
  Reads diagrams, selectedDiagramId, and all diagram actions from the session store using shallow comparison.
  Derives selectedDiagram by calling the store's getSelectedDiagram getter.
  Exposes: diagrams, selectedDiagramId, selectedDiagram, addDiagram, updateDiagram, removeDiagram,
  selectDiagram, setDiagrams, getDiagramById, hasDiagram.

---

FUNCTION getDiagramById(id) -> Diagram | undefined
  Finds and returns the diagram with the given id from the current list, or undefined if not found.

---

FUNCTION hasDiagram(id) -> boolean
  Returns true if a diagram with the given id exists in the current list.
